T1  - The effect of a rating change announcement on bond price
AU  - Weinstein, Mark I.
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 5
IS  - 3
SP  - 329
EP  - 350
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/12/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(77)90042-3
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X77900423
AB  - This paper examines the behavior of corporate bond prices during the period surrounding the announcement of a rating change. We find some evidence of price change during the period from 18 to 7 months before the rating change is announced. We find no evidence of any reaction during the 6 months prior to the rating change. We also find little reaction, if any, during the month of the change or for 6 months after the change. This evidence contradicts the recent findings of Katz and Grier and Katz.
ER  - 

